  <section>
    <p class="overline">Overview</p>
    <h2>What MyPaas is</h2>
    <p>
      MyPaas is a self-hosted PaaS control plane for one Linux server. It accepts
      repositories with an explicit deployment contract, runs the workload on
      Docker or publishes ready static output through Caddy, and keeps operational
      state in a dashboard.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is built for an owner and a small whitelist of trusted collaborators.
      It is not a hosted service, public registration system, or multi-tenant cloud.
    </p>
    <aside class="note">
      <p>
        These docs describe current behavior from the product requirements,
        repository changelog, installer, and implementation. Roadmap items are
        not presented as available features.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Supported project contracts</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Mode</th><th>Repository requirement</th><th>Runtime</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Dockerfile</strong></td><td>Root <code>Dockerfile</code> and an application port.</td><td>One application container.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Docker Compose</strong></td><td>A Compose file at the root or in a subdirectory — auto-discovered or set explicitly — plus a selected public service.</td><td>Main service plus private supporting services.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Static</strong></td><td>Ready <code>index.html</code> in <code>dist</code>, <code>build</code>, <code>public</code>, or root.</td><td>Caddy file server without an app container.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      Detection priority is Compose, then Dockerfile, then static output. Compose
      discovery walks the repository tree (depth ≤ 4), ranks root files highest, and
      skips dependency and build-output directories; the chosen path is persisted so
      webhook redeploys use the same file. Detection prepares a plan; the user still
      reviews branch, ports, resources, and environment values.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>System model</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li><strong>GitHub</strong> provides repository access, OAuth identity, and signed push events.</li>
      <li><strong>MyPaas</strong> validates the project, queues deployment work, and stores operational state.</li>
      <li><strong>Docker and Compose</strong> build and run project workloads on the host.</li>
      <li><strong>Caddy</strong> maps project hostnames to local runtime ports or static files.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare Tunnel</strong> provides configured public ingress and TLS.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

